 of childhood. Drawing on an extensive range of sources that illuminate teaching practice, from school logbooks to oral histories, this book will be crucial not only for historians and sociologists of modern Britain, but for education professionals and policy-makers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEarly childhood educationzGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 0aEducationzGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 0aProgressive educationzGreat Britain. 7aHISTORY / Social History.2bisacsh  aAdolescence.  aChildhood.  aClass.  aEducation.  aGender.  aPedagogy.  aPsychoanalysis.  aPsychology.  aQuality education.  aSchooling.  aYouth.1 aTisdall, Laura, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packagez978311128248040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152613290140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526132901423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526132901/original  a978-3-11-128248-0  Manchester University Press 2020 eBook-Packageb2020  aGBV-deGruyter-alles